    thinking: "**Clarifying User Intent**\n\nI\'m focusing on the user\'s question, which seems informational. My priority is providing a clear explanation. I\'ll hold off on offering improvements unless explicitly requested. I should also quickly check my system to ensure everything is in order.\n\n\n**Addressing Customization Requests**\n\nI\'m now formulating a plan for addressing user queries about customization. I\'ll explain the mechanisms, focusing on `AGENTS.md` and `GEMINI.md`, and detail how they are loaded. I\'ll also explain why I don\'t create these files by default, emphasizing functional code over unsolicited documentation. I will always offer help with creating or updating `AGENTS.md` to capture project context or rules.\n\n\n**Refining Value Proposition**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on a user-centric guide for maximizing value from our interactions. I\'m prioritizing clarity and conversational tone, tailoring explanations to user queries, and focusing on practical aspects like customization via `AGENTS.md` and `GEMINI.md`. I am ensuring this guide is both friendly and professional, providing information without excessive jargon. My aim is to deliver a concise and impactful document.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "To get the absolute best out of me as your developer in Google AI Studio, here are the most effective strategies and patterns you can use:\n\n### 1. Be Direct and Explicit with Your Goals\nI perform best when you specify **exactly what you want to achieve** in a literal, conversational way.\n*   **Specify user-facing behavior:** Instead of saying *\"Optimise the app,\"* say *\"Add a search bar to the invoice list screen that filters by party name or invoice number in real time.\"*\n*   **Mention visual and aesthetic preferences:** If you have a specific mood in mind, define it simply. For example: *\"Center the layout inside an elegant high-contrast dark card using monospace typography for numerical dates and totals.\"*\n\n### 2. Connect Your Real Data (No Mock Data)\nIf you need to connect your real account or services (e.g., *\"my Google Drive,\"* *\"my calendar,\"* or *\"my Firebase account\"*), state it explicitly. Rather than injecting fake mock data, I will provision actual backend integrations, configure secure API pathways on your server, and guide you through setting up real OAuth consent gates so the application works with your authentic data.\n\n### 3. Persist Your Rules using `AGENTS.md`\nIf you have persistent guidelines, project-specific rules, or style definitions that apply to your entire application, we can save them in a file named `AGENTS.md` (or `GEMINI.md`) in the root directory. \n*   **The Customization Mechanism:** The system automatically reads `AGENTS.md` and appends its contents directly to my developer instructions every turn.\n*   **What to put there:** You can document constraints such as your target database structure, preferred Tailwind accent colors, navigation patterns, or rules like *\"Always translate financial terms or keep them to standard double-entry accounting notation.\"*\n\n### How would you like to proceed?\nIf you\'d like, **I can create a tailored `AGENTS.md` file for you right now** to lock in your preferred design patterns and project scope, or you can describe the next feature you want to build inside this application!"
    thinking_duration {
