    thinking: "**Assessing User Intent**\n\nI\'ve homed in on the user\'s intent: they\'re seeking information. Specifically, they want to understand a capability of the environment\342\200\224whether it supports the creation of multiple agents. I\'m focusing on the informational nature of the query, so I can respond appropriately. Let\'s see how this affects our response.\n\n\n**Formulating Clear Explanation**\n\nI\'m now formulating a clear explanation to address the user\'s questions. I\'ve analyzed the query\'s informational core and decided to base the response on the context. I have decided to explain how the user can configure custom rules or agent behaviors by looking at `AGENTS.md` and `GEMINI.md`. All the skills are irrelevant, since the question is about an informational intent.\n\n\n**Refining Guidance Strategies**\n\nI am now focusing on refining my guidance strategies. I will suggest adding instructions to `AGENTS.md` when the user offers repetitive advice or project-specific rules. I\'ll also proactively offer assistance in creating or updating these files. I can explain the customization process, including persistent rules and project conventions, with links to relevant documentation. I can also explain the default behaviors.\n\n\n"
